===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} ''[[plege#Middle English|plege]]'' from {{etyl|xno}} ''[[plege#Anglo-Norman|plege]]'' from {{etyl|fro}} ''[[plege#Old French|plege]]'' (Modern {{fr}} ''[[pleige]]'') from {{etyl|ML.}} ''[[plevium]]'', ''[[plebium]]'' from {{etyl|ML.}} ''[[plebire]]'' "to pledge", of {{etyl|gem}} origin, from {{etyl|frk}} *{{term||plegan|to pledge, support, guarantee}} from {{proto|Germanic|plegō|responsibility, habit|lang=}} from {{proto|Indo-European|dlegh-||lang=}}. Akin to {{etyl|goh|-}} {{term|pflegan||lang=goh|to take care of, be accustomed to}}, {{etyl|osx|-}} {{term|plegan|lang=osx||to vouch for}}, {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|pleon|lang=ang|plēon|to risk, endanger}}. More at [[plight]].

